CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed and untitled report under the rubric "Official </F>
Chronicle"] 
  [Text] On 23 March Zhirair Liparityan, Republic of Armenia 
first deputy minister of foreign affairs, met with an official 
NATO delegation headed by NATO Deputy Secretary General Tugay 
Ozseri. 
  An ARMENPRESS reporter was told in the department of press 
and public relations of the Republic of Armenia MID [Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs] that among the items discussed at the meeting 
were the provisions of the Partnership for Peace program 
proposed by NATO in January of this year to East European and 
former USSR states. 
  The Armenian authorities are currently contemplating the 
issue of Armenia's participation in this program. 

</TEXT>

