<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Nothing To Pay With?"] </F>
  [Text] During the course of 1993 Turkmenistan shipped 8.5 
billion cubic meters of gas to Azerbaijan. To date, however, the 
Republic of Azerbaijan has not paid a single kopek to the 
suppliers. Baku radio reports that unless the Cabinet of 
Ministers undertakes extreme measures, Azerbaijan may find 
itself without gas. 

