of sheep and goats dropped by almost 1.5 million head, and in 
Uzbekistan--by 142,000. Herd reductions occurred mainly at 
agricultural enterprises, while their number at the population's 
private plots increased. However, the increased share of herd 
owned by the population has not made up for its decline at 
agricultural enterprises. Changes in the size of the livestock 
