of the current year as compared to January 1993. The greatest 
decline occurred in Azerbaijan--by 14 kg (17 percent), 
Kyrgyzstan--by 13 kg (8 percent), and Russia--by 10 kg (by 7 
percent). In Turkmenistan, Belarus, and Ukraine the average 
yield of milk per cow increased over this period by 7 kg (by 4.6 
percent). 
